is a stratified Datalogprop view. DRed maintenance costs per update versus for recomputation, with an explicit family witnessing an asymptotic gap. is decidable in polynomial time. Any correct incremental algorithm must probe all atoms in .
2.3 Beyond-RAG Conversation Understanding
Agrawal, Gummuluri, and Spera [1] map each conversation turn to a canonical question and routing decision . FAQ-matched queries are answered by direct retrieval (2 s); novel queries proceed through RAG with improved query formulation. The module produces the resolved intent driving capability assembly at Stage 2.
2.4 MultiWOZ 2.2
MultiWOZ 2.2 [4, 22] contains 10,438 human-human task-oriented dialogues across 8 domains (hotel, restaurant, attraction, taxi, train, hospital, police, general), split 8,438 / 1,000 / 1,000 (train/val/test), mean 13.7 turns, Apache 2.0 and MIT licenced. Each turn has a belief state (slot-value dictionary of cumulative user intent) and dialogue act annotations.
We use MultiWOZ for two purposes: (1) as input to Algorithm 1—the MultiWOZ 2.2 ontology and published co-occurrence statistics are the extraction corpus; and (2) as a test corpus for the session closure model—belief states at each turn serve as ground-truth capability sets , making the Completeness Assumption verifiable by construction.
